<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 06 at 2:56PM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of central Blaine
County through 315 PM MDT...
At 255 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 20
miles northwest of Hays, moving north at 5 mph.
HAZARD...Penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Cleveland.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM MDT for
north central Montana.</instruction>
